    dc:date "2016" ;
    dc:title "Hill forest dweller: a new cryptic species of Rhinolophus in the ‘ pusillus group’ (Chiroptera: Rhinolophidae) from Thailand and Lao PDR" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756732>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756734>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756736>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756738>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756740>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756742>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756744>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756746>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756748> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756732>
    dc:description "FIG. 1. Type locality and distribution of R. monticolus sp. nov. (black triangles) and the localities of specimens of R. shortridgei (open squares), R. lepidus (open circles), R. refulgens (black circles) and R. pusillus (asterisks) that were examined in this study" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3756732/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756734>
    dc:description "FIG. 2. Noseleaf (a–c) and dorsal (d) and ventral (e) pelage of R. monticolus sp. nov. PSUZC-MM2013.14 (paratype) from Thailand. Not to scale" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3756734/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756736>
    dc:description "FIG. 3. Lateral and dorsal views of the skull of (a) R. monticolus sp. nov. ♂ PSUZC-MM2008.1 (holotype) from Thailand, and (b) R. shortridgei ♂ BMNH. 18.8.3.1 (holotype) from Myanmar. Scale bar = 5 mm" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3756736/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756738>
    dc:description "FIG. 4. Occlusal view of the upper and lower toothrows of (a) R. monticolus sp. nov. ♂ PSUZC-MM2008.1 (holotype) from Thailand, and (b) R. shortridgei ♂ BMNH. 18.8.3.1 (holotype) from Myanmar. Scale bar = 5 mm" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3756738/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756740>
    dc:description "FIG. 5. Dorsal (left) and lateral views (right) of the baculum of (a) R. monticolus sp. nov. PSUZC-MM2013.14 (paratype) from Thailand, and (b) R. shortridgei PSUZC-MM2010.7 from Myanmar. Scale bar = 2 mm" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3756740/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756742>
    dc:description "FIG. 6. Biplot between FA and SL of male (a) and female (b) specimens of R. monticolus sp. nov. (black diamonds), R. shortridgei (open squares) from Myanmar, R. lepidus (black circles = specimens from India; open circles = specimens from Myanmar, Vietnam, Cambodia and Thailand), R. refulgens from S. Thailand and Malaysia (asterisks), R. pusillus (open triangles) from Thailand, and R. acuminatus (crosses) from Thailand" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3756742/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756744>
    dc:description "FIG. 7. Principle component analysis (PCA) based on 11 craniodental measurements of 91 specimens of R. monticolus sp. nov. (diamonds), R. shortridgei (squares) from Myanmar, R. lepidus from India, Myanmar, Vietnam, Cambodia and Thailand (circles), R. refulgens from S. Thailand and Malaysia (asterisks and crosses), and R. pusillus from Thailand (triangles). The different shaded symbols represent male and female specimens of each species. The factor loading scores are included in Table 4" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3756744/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756746>
    dc:description "FIG. 8. Bayesian tree based on based on 41 cyt b sequences of bats from East and Southeast Asia using GTR+I+G model. The node labels indicate posterior probability values. The genetic distances within and between species are presented in Table 5. Specimens included in this analysis are listed in Appendix II" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3756746/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3756748>
    dc:description "FIG. 9. Bayesian tree based on 183 COI sequences of bats from East and Southeast Asia using GTR+I+G model. The node labels indicate posterior probability values. The genetic distances within and between species are presented in Table 6. For the pusillus- group, the country names where specimens were collected are given. Specimens included in this analysis are listed in Appendix III" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3756748/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

